ective of the substrate input. Substrate quality in the rhizosphere and detritusphere affected enzyme activities only in the topsoil, whereas a sharp decline of C input with depth led to similar activities in the subsoil. Most of the enzyme indexes reflected shifts in allocation of C and nutrients in the rhizosphere and detritusphere. The presented results underline the role of microorganisms as critical links in the C and nutrient transfers in the rhizosphere and detritusphere.},
